project-root/
│
├── playwright.config.ts        # Playwright configuration
├── package.json                # Dependencies & scripts
│
├── tests/
       ui/                       # UI Test files
│       ├── login.test.ts
│       ├── cart.test.ts
│       └── order.test.ts          
│
│       api/                       # API Test files
│       ├── cart.test.ts
│       └── order.test.ts  
├── pages/                       # Page Object Models (POMs)
│   ├── basePage.ts
│   ├── loginPage.ts
│   ├── homePage.ts
│   ├── cartPage.ts
│   └── orderPage.ts             
│
├── testData/                    # Centralized test data in json file to generate multiple tests dynamically
|
|
├── utils/                      # Helpers 
│   └── alertHelpers.ts 
│ 
├── api/                      # api methods and andpoints 
     ├── apiEndpoints.ts
     └── cartApiHelpers.ts   



### Keys for isolation, speed, and maintainability
  - The Page Object Model (POM) is applied to page classes, encapsulate all the messy selectors and UI interactions
  - Each test runs in a completely separate browser context
  - Each test runs with indipendent test data
  - JSON file holds test data (category + product).
  - Test Loop through JSON to generate multiple tests dynamically.
  - Validating API Calls Triggered by the UI to monitor network traffic during UI interactions
  - Test Suites (test.describe): Group related tests for readability and modularity.
  - Tests can run fullyParallel in both CI and Local
  - Tests retry on fisrt failure

### Run tests
- Run all ui tests in 3 browsers and api tests 1 time:  npx playwright test
- Run a specific test file with chrome: npx playwright test --project=chromium ./test/order.spec.ts
- Run Api test: npx playwright test --project=API
